{
  "video_id": "ZMThW10wQa0",
  "title": "Why Humans Can't Regrow Teeth",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 300.0,
      "end_time": 3750.0,
      "text": "- [Narrator] Humans need dentists. It's a fact."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3750.0,
      "end_time": 5558.0,
      "text": "In 2017 alone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 5558.0,
      "end_time": 10549.0,
      "text": "Americans spent $129 billion on dental visits,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 10960.0,
      "end_time": 15740.0,
      "text": "and an estimated 90% of adults in the US have fillings."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 15740.0,
      "end_time": 17870.0,
      "text": "But many animals don't have this problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 17870.0,
      "end_time": 20390.0,
      "text": "because they can regrow their teeth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 20390.0,
      "end_time": 25390.0,
      "text": "replacing old damaged ones with brand new pearly whites."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 25460.0,
      "end_time": 27860.0,
      "text": "Wouldn't it be great if you could do that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 27860.0,
      "end_time": 30689.0,
      "text": "Well, there's actually an important trade-off"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 30690.0,
      "end_time": 32430.0,
      "text": "for this nuisance."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 35155.0,
      "end_time": 39400.0,
      "text": "Only a handful of mammals can regrow teeth multiple times"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39400.0,
      "end_time": 43900.0,
      "text": "compared to the 50,000 species of reptiles and fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 43900.0,
      "end_time": 46220.0,
      "text": "Take geckos for example."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 46220.0,
      "end_time": 51220.0,
      "text": "They replace all 100 or so teeth every three to four months,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51720.0,
      "end_time": 54940.0,
      "text": "and since geckos can live for six to 10 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 54940.0,
      "end_time": 57250.0,
      "text": "they'll grow anywhere from 1,800"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 57250.0,
      "end_time": 60330.0,
      "text": "to 4,000 teeth in a lifetime."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 60330.0,
      "end_time": 63739.0,
      "text": "That's all thanks to a special type of cell in their gums"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63740.0,
      "end_time": 65680.0,
      "text": "called stem cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 65680.0,
      "end_time": 68730.0,
      "text": "Stem cells are handy because they can morph into different"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 68730.0,
      "end_time": 70170.0,
      "text": "cells when needed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 70170.0,
      "end_time": 73133.0,
      "text": "like tooth stem cells to build new teeth."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 73133.0,
      "end_time": 75880.0,
      "text": "Humans have these stem cells when we're younger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 75880.0,
      "end_time": 78890.0,
      "text": "but after our adult teeth grow in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 78900.0,
      "end_time": 80930.0,
      "text": "the stem cells die and disappear."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 80930.0,
      "end_time": 83920.0,
      "text": "To understand why, let's take a journey back in time"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 83920.0,
      "end_time": 88490.0,
      "text": "to about 320 million years ago when mammals"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 88490.0,
      "end_time": 90800.0,
      "text": "and reptiles split off."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 90800.0,
      "end_time": 93270.0,
      "text": "In addition to many obvious differences,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 93270.0,
      "end_time": 97259.0,
      "text": "another change that eventually emerged was tooth shape."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 97260.0,
      "end_time": 100660.0,
      "text": "Reptiles, for example, are what's called generalists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 100660.0,
      "end_time": 104220.0,
      "text": "meaning they eat the animals they can get their teeth on."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 104220.0,
      "end_time": 107640.0,
      "text": "And for that, they needed teeth with the same size and shape"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 107640.0,
      "end_time": 110760.0,
      "text": "to keep prey from escaping their mouths."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 110760.0,
      "end_time": 114700.0,
      "text": "Mammals, on the other hand, developed more specific diets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 114700.0,
      "end_time": 119400.0,
      "text": "like grazers who only eat grass and hunters who rip flesh"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 119400.0,
      "end_time": 120610.0,
      "text": "from their kills."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 120610.0,
      "end_time": 123830.0,
      "text": "As a result, mammals evolved different-shaped teeth"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 123830.0,
      "end_time": 125510.0,
      "text": "for different purposes."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 125510.0,
      "end_time": 127760.0,
      "text": "And it's this difference that could also explain"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 127760.0,
      "end_time": 130590.0,
      "text": "why mammals can't regrow more teeth."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 130590.0,
      "end_time": 134200.0,
      "text": "Now, let's say you could regrow your molars multiple times,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 134200.0,
      "end_time": 135399.0,
      "text": "for example."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 135400.0,
      "end_time": 138650.0,
      "text": "It's important that the top and bottom sets match up."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 138650.0,
      "end_time": 142800.0,
      "text": "Otherwise, they can't grind food as efficiently."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 142800.0,
      "end_time": 145600.0,
      "text": "That sounds good in principle, but with each new set,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 145600.0,
      "end_time": 148760.0,
      "text": "there's a risk that the regrown teeth won't line up."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 148760.0,
      "end_time": 152802.0,
      "text": "So the leading theory is that adult humans can't regrow"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 152802.0,
      "end_time": 154410.0,
      "text": "our teeth because it was better for survival"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 154410.0,
      "end_time": 158310.0,
      "text": "to only grow one well-aligned adult set."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 158310.0,
      "end_time": 161520.0,
      "text": "However, if you still wish you could regrow a tooth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 161520.0,
      "end_time": 163820.0,
      "text": "there may be a way in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 163820.0,
      "end_time": 167970.0,
      "text": "Using lasers and drugs, scientists have helped rats and mice"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 167970.0,
      "end_time": 172228.0,
      "text": "regrow damaged tissue in cavity-ridden teeth"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 172229.0,
      "end_time": 175840.0,
      "text": "with the idea that if you could regrow tooth tissue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 175840.0,
      "end_time": 179290.0,
      "text": "you could eventually regrow entire teeth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 179290.0,
      "end_time": 183579.0,
      "text": "though no human testing has been done on that yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 183580.0,
      "end_time": 186570.0,
      "text": "So keep flossing and keep seeing your dentist."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 186570.0,
      "end_time": 187593.0,
      "text": "At least for now."
    }
  ]
}